[src:snapshot-testing/snapshot-testing] Snapshot testing and visual regression testing are two distinct ways of testing UIs, and they serve different purposes.
[src:snapshot-testing/snapshot-testing] Visual regression testing tools take screenshots of web pages and compare the resulting images pixel by pixel.
[src:snapshot-testing/snapshot-testing] With Snapshot testing values are serialized, stored within text files, and compared using a diff algorithm.
[src:snapshot-testing/snapshot-testing] There are different trade-offs to consider and we listed the reasons why snapshot testing was built in the Jest blog.
[src:snapshot-testing/snapshot-testing] Snapshot testing is only one of more than 20 assertions that ship with Jest.
