[src:snapshot-testing/software-testing-p02] Clinically defined, a test case is an input and an expected result.
[src:snapshot-testing/software-testing-p02] This can be as terse as "for condition x your derived result is y", although normally test cases describe in more detail the input scenario and what results might be expected.
[src:snapshot-testing/software-testing-p02] It can occasionally be a series of steps (but often steps are contained in a separate test procedure that can be exercised against multiple test cases, as a matter of economy) but with one expected result or expected outcome.
